				\begin{document}$${\sigma }_{1}$$\end{document}) of the A exciton intensities as functions of photon energy and temperature for various thicknesses are represented in Fig. 3d. Here, we clearly observe almost temperature-independent exciton binding energies for all three 2H-MoTe2 film samples (see Fig. 3c) since both the peak position of exciton A and the direct bandgap edge at K- point show almost the same temperature-dependence (see Fig. 3d). The error bars in the bandgap edge curves are the confidence levels of the bandgap edge.

